Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
enc_tcl_return_display_limit(25.10)        enc_tcl_return_display_limit(25.10)

Name
       enc_tcl_return_display_limit

Syntax
       enc_tcl_return_display_limit <value>

       Type: Integer

       Default: 10000

       You  can use this variable to set the number of characters displayed on
       the xterm window (stdout) and the .log file. The Tcl return  value  it-
       self is not truncated. A value of -1 indicates that there is no display
       limit.  The  Tcl  return value of the history command will not be trun-
       cated by setting this variable.

Example
              * In the example below, the tcl return values  of  getDesignMode
                command options are not truncated. However, the remaining part
                is truncated to 3 characters.

                innovus 1> set enc_tcl_return_display_limit 3

                innovus 2> getDesignMode

                -addPhysicalCell  hier                    # enums={hier flat},
                default=hier

                -congEffort auto                         #  enums={low  medium
                high auto}, default=auto

                -dual_rail_via_pitch {}                 # string, default=""""

                -earlyClockFlow false                   # bool, default=false

                -expressRoute false                     # bool, default=false

                -flowEffort standard                    # enums={express stan-
                dard extreme}, default=standard

                -ignore_followpin_vias false            # bool, default=false

                -pessimisticMode  false                  # enums={true false},
                default=false

                -powerEffort  none                        #  enums={none   low
                high}, default=none

                -process  90                              #  int,  default=90,
                min=3, max=250

                -slackWeighting unityWeighting          #  enums={unityWeight-
                ing viewBasedWeighting}, default=unityWeighting

                {ad...  truncated to 3 characters (use the enc_tcl_return_dis-
                play_limit variable to control the length before truncation).

              * In  the  example  below,  the  value  of   enc_tcl_return_dis-
                play_limit  is  set  to  -1.  As a result, there is no display
                limit.

                innovus 3> set enc_tcl_return_display_limit -1

                -1

                innovus 4> getDesignMode

                -addPhysicalCell hier # enums={hier flat}, default=hier

                -congEffort auto # enums={low medium high auto}, default=auto

                -dual_rail_via_pitch {} # string, default=""

                -earlyClockFlow false # bool, default=false

                -expressRoute false # bool, default=false

                -flowEffort standard # enums={express standard  extreme},  de-
                fault=standard

                -ignore_followpin_vias false # bool, default=false

                -pessimisticMode false # enums={true false}, default=false

                -powerEffort none # enums={none low high}, default=none

                -process 90 # int, default=90, min=3, max=250

                -slackWeighting  unityWeighting  # enums={unityWeighting view-
                BasedWeighting}, default=unityWeighting

                {addPhysicalCell hier} {congEffort auto}  {dual_rail_via_pitch
                {}}  {earlyClockFlow  false}  {expressRoute false} {flowEffort
                standard}   {ignore_followpin_vias   false}   {pessimisticMode
                false}  {powerEffort none} {process 90} {slackWeighting unity-
                Weighting}

